Introduction

EJel, also known as Chang Eun Jeong and Augusteng, is a South Korean singer-songwriter under MNH Entertainment.

She was a semi-final contestant on the Mnet 2020/2021 survival show Folk Us and the TV Chosun 2023 survival show Show Queen. She finished in third place on the JTBC 2023/2024 survival show Sing Again 3. She is also a member of the cover duo Seraffine.

Fun facts

1
EJel competed as the masked singer "Sunrise" on the MBC singing competition variety show "King of Mask Singer" during episode 480 & 481 on January 26 & February 2, 2025. She performed "Love Is Like a Glass" by Woo Junhee (against Baek Bong-ki), "Romantic Cat" by Cherry Filter (against Wonjin of CRAVITY), and "In Dreams" by Lena Park (against Taehyun of Dickpunks).
…
2
EJel performed a cover of "Sugarcoat" (KISS OF LIFE Natty Solo) on KBS "The Seasons: Rainbow of Lee Young Ji" during episode 8 on November 22, 2024.
…
3
EJel performed her song "Now or Never", "Issues" (by Julia Michaels) with Pharita (BABYMONSTER), "Amor" (by Baek A) with Jukjae, "Congratulations" by DAY6, and "Birds of a Feather" by Billie Eilish on "Begin Again Open Mic" in 2024.
…
4
EJel became friends with Seeun (STAYC) and Jihan (Weeekly) when they were trainees together at Plan A Entertainment. Both of them showed up to support EJel when she was competing in the final round of the JTBC survival show "Sing Again 3" during episode 13 on January 18, 2024.
…
5
EJel became friends with Lee Seoyeon (fromis_9) when they were classmates at SOPA (School of Performing Arts Seoul).
…
6
EJel created her stage name by combining her birth name "Eun Jeong" and the word "easel" which is used for drawing/painting art. She used to use the stage name "Augusteng" until she changed it to "EJel" in September 2023.
…
7
EJel won a bronze award at the "33rd Yoo Jae Ha Music Contest" singer/songwriter competition for her song "After This Blue Summer" on November 12, 2022. She performed the song during the JTBC survival show "Sing Again 3" on December 28, 2023.
…
8
EJel is a member of a CCM cover duo called "Seraffine" with her friend Jung Seul who finished in 7th place in the final round of TV Chosun's 2024 survival show "Miss Trot 3".
…
